<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057110-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 8 and b = 7. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
A = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>10.6</li><li>48.8</li><li>41.2</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={8}^{{2}}+{7}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={64}+{49}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={113}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{113}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{10.630145812735}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{10.6}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{7}}\right)}}}\approx{48.81407483429}\approx{48.8}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{48.81407483429}^{\circ}\approx{41.18592516571}\approx{41.2}</m>.</p>

</solution>
